  "texts": [
    "Finally, notice that the notion of local system on ∂ that we will be using here to describe the formal data of connections is closely related to the one of 2πZ-equivariant local system on R which is used in [Moc25]: Lemma 2.5.",
    "A local system on S 1 is the same as a 2πZ-equivariant local system on R.",
    "If V 0 is a local system on S 1 and τ: R → S 1, x → e ix is the universal covering, then τ -1 V 0 is a 2πZ-equivariant local system on R. The inverse construction is also easily described.",
